  "inline_comments": [
    {
      "id": "38fb0563_7de23553",
      "file_path": "sdnr/wt/netconfnode-state-service/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/features/sdnr/wt/netconfnodestateservice/impl/access/binding/GenericTransactionUtils.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 111,
      "message": "This change is breaking the opendaylight cluster scenario. \nReason: The implicite close is not handled correctly by underlaying opendaylight netconf service.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4931,
        "name": "Herbert Eiselt",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "herbert.eiselt@highstreet-technologies.com",
        "username": "highstreetherbert"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-20 14:12:43.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "ebfa72bb_f134873c",
      "file_path": "sdnr/wt/netconfnode-state-service/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/features/sdnr/wt/netconfnodestateservice/impl/access/binding/GenericTransactionUtils.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 111,
      "message": "Not sure I understand :) \nThe goald is to close readTransaction at the end. \nThe problem is only with the implicite close ? You mean, I just need to add a line \"readTransaction.close()\" for an explicite close or just we can't close readTransaction ?\n\nI also do the same on ODLEventListenerHandler :(\n\nSonar issue : https://sonarcloud.io/project/issues?id=onap_ccsdk-features&issues=AXIslx6i0PGsbkeF8ODB&open=AXIslx6i0PGsbkeF8ODB",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7700,
        "name": "Samuel Liard",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "samuel.liard@gmail.com",
        "username": "sliard"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-20 14:22:59.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "38fb0563_7de23553",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "e5889cc9_8cfbc69e",
      "file_path": "sdnr/wt/netconfnode-state-service/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/features/sdnr/wt/netconfnodestateservice/impl/conf/odlGeo/ClusterRoleInfo.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 28,
      "message": "See at multiple places:\n\n\"*\" needs to be replaced with {0,1024}\nI think 1024 is a valid magnitude for the strings.\nBut the generic assumption for digits to have only 10 is risky .. should be also {0,1024}\n\nUsed Java 7 regex defintion;\nX*\t-> X, zero or more times\nX{n,m}  -> at least n but not more than m times\nhttps://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4931,
        "name": "Herbert Eiselt",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "herbert.eiselt@highstreet-technologies.com",
        "username": "highstreetherbert"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-20 14:31:14.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "61c2f67b_58ae22e7",
      "file_path": "sdnr/wt/netconfnode-state-service/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/features/sdnr/wt/netconfnodestateservice/impl/conf/odlGeo/ClusterRoleInfo.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 28,
      "message": "Yes, I'm agree X* is zero or more times. \nBut in this case it was maybe a mistake. \nLook at the parsing after : \"Integer.parseInt(matcher.group(2));\"\nThat will return an exception if string is empty... so maybe {1,1024} is more secure no ?\n\nBut ok to change {1,10} with {1,1024}",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7700,
        "name": "Samuel Liard",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "samuel.liard@gmail.com",
        "username": "sliard"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-20 14:39:25.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e5889cc9_8cfbc69e",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "4679cf69_60e0a72f",
      "file_path": "sdnr/wt/netconfnode-state-service/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/features/sdnr/wt/netconfnodestateservice/impl/access/binding/GenericTransactionUtils.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 111,
      "message": "I am refering to this: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/tryResourceClose.html\n\nThe try(ressources) is always implicitely closing the transaction per java definition. \nBut the \"close\" in opendaylight netconf service is not correctly implemented and will terminate the read immediately. Because of this opendaylight problem this change can not be done. Or in other words the close of the transaction must never be called, because of wrong implementation. \n\nNot all Sonarqube errors or warnings make sense, because sonarqube is not knowing such specifics. Excuse me to say that ;-)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4931,
        "name": "Herbert Eiselt",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "herbert.eiselt@highstreet-technologies.com",
        "username": "highstreetherbert"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-20 14:52:13.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ebfa72bb_f134873c",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9c9f1e89_828c9d4c",
      "file_path": "sdnr/wt/netconfnode-state-service/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/features/sdnr/wt/netconfnodestateservice/impl/access/binding/GenericTransactionUtils.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 111,
      "message": "You are totally right :)\nNot all sonar problems have to be solved.\n\nI will rollback all my changes like this one.\n\nBut I found some case where you have already closed the transaction :\nhttps://github.com/onap/ccsdk-features/blob/c8f7e3f376992b202ba26464b9b329d6c4b2821d/sdnr/wt/data-provider/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/features/sdnr/wt/dataprovider/impl/DataProviderServiceImpl.java#L430\n\nAt least 4 times (not a lot) Should I also change them ?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7700,
        "name": "Samuel Liard",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "samuel.liard@gmail.com",
        "username": "sliard"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-20 15:05:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "4679cf69_60e0a72f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "700885e6_1b672df9",
